CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 3, 1950, pg. 5, reads: "Church Burns - This hole in floor of the St. Philip [Phillip] African Orthodox Science Church at 131 Crawford Street resulted here Monday when a $1,200 fire raged through the structure. Pews on the first floor can be seen and on the basement level, the rows of folding chairs used in the church services. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Interior of fire damaged St. Phillip African Orthodox Science Church with large hole in floor revealing rows of folding chairs on floor below, and banner draped over pew that reads "ORTHODOX Science-Church MISSIONARIES"
